Description: Backport timekeeping, task-state, and mmap read-lock APIs
 Modern kernels removed do_gettimeofday()/struct timeval from reachable
 module code, made task_struct::state private, and renamed mmap_sem to the
 mmap read-lock helper API. Add feature-probed 367.134 compatibility wrappers
 preserving wall-clock microsecond semantics, public scheduler state updates,
 raw-monotonic UVM timing, and local/remote GUP locking semantics.
Origin: backport, adapted for NVIDIA 367.134 from later NVIDIA/Debian API compatibility patterns
Forwarded: not-needed

